description_html: Here is a gallery containing the spiritual portraits of a couple of my cousins.
story_html:
I have a few more cousins and will contact them soon, so hopefully I can add a few more portraits to this gallery.

To keep up to date, follow this site on social media or join the SeeOurMinds.com email list!

image_list.title: Lin C
image_list.subtitle_html: Works for NASA
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: Lin is a cousin on my father's side.  She works for NASA.  Click on the image to learn more!
image_list.explain_dom: The Yellow in this spiritual portrait represents Lin's dominant trait, her pragmatism.  In Introverts, the dominant trait is directed inwardly, and spiritual portraits use a long horizontal line to represent this.
image_list.explain_aux: The Green in this spiritual portrait represents Lin's auxiliary trait, her rationality.  In Introverts, the auxiliary trait is directed outwardly, and spiritual portraits use a vertical line to represent this, because it is more evident than the dominant function.
image_list.story_html:
Lin lives in Virginia.

Once the site is in fairly decent shape, I will let her know I've posted her portrait, and hopefully get her permission to post more information.

image_list.title: Oren B
image_list.subtitle_html: Technical Manager at Air National Guard Recruiting
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: Oren is a cousin on my mother's side.  He works for the Air National Guard.  Click on the image to learn more!
image_list.explain_dom: The Blue in this spiritual portrait represents Oren's dominant trait, his idealism.  In Introverts, the dominant trait is directed inwardly, and spiritual portraits use a long horizontal line to represent this.
image_list.explain_aux: The Green in this spiritual portrait represents Oren's auxiliary trait, his rationality.  In Introverts, the auxiliary trait is directed outwardly, and spiritual portraits use a vertical line to represent this, because it is more evident than the dominant function.
image_list.story_html:
Oren lives in Oregon.

Once the site is in fairly decent shape, I will let him know I've posted his portrait, and hopefully get his permission to post more information.
